## Plan for independence

When creating a multi-PR plan, **maximize the number of PRs that can be worked on in parallel**:

- Prefer slicing by vertical feature or module so PRs don't touch the same files.
- Explicitly mark each PR as **independent** or list its dependency (e.g. "depends on PR 2").
- Independent PRs each get a worktree from `origin/main`; a dependent PR gets a new worktree from `origin/main` only after its prerequisite merges.

## One PR per worktree, many worktrees in parallel

We work with **git worktrees** (one per PR) so we can have several PRs in flight in parallel via Mission Control and **coding-session** agent work (one session per worktree).

- Inside any single worktree, implement **at most one PR** at a time.
- Do **not** put commits for separate planned PRs in the same worktree.
- Do **not** stack worktrees or PRs unless the developer explicitly asks for it.
- When a PR is done, open it for review; the next independent PR is already being worked on in another worktree.

## Review before commit

After implementing changes, **stop**. Do not `git add`, `git commit`, or `git push` until the developer explicitly confirms that we are ready to move on to the next development stage.

- Present a summary of what changed and ask for next steps using `AskQuestion`. 
- This applies to **all** workflows: feature PRs, PR comment fixes, and any other code changes.
- **Pre-review verification (hosting repo):** Before the summary and review modal / ship cut-point, complete **pre-review verification** prescribed by applicable **hosting-repo** **`.cursor/rules/*.mdc`** files. Resolve which rules apply from the PR plan **§5**, **Project rules** curation in **`coding-session`**, or rules already loaded from the worktree — per [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/rules/40_maintain-rules.mdc`](40_maintain-rules.mdc). Do **not** duplicate hosting-repo commands in center rules or skills. Do not open developer review until prescribed verification passes (**exit 0**); fix failures and re-run.
- The exceptions are creating worktrees (fine without confirmation). The coding agent must not silently commit. After developer approves implementation at the ship cut-point, `coding-session` commits (with explicit consent), runs **Before deploy** via inline **`deploy-walk`** when applicable, then **auto-spawns** the `pre-pr-review` reviewer lane (no separate pre-PR spawn modal).

**Sedea git gate (same message):** This section is a **workflow** pause — it does **not** replace [`.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/6_git-commit-push-gate.mdc`](.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/6_git-commit-push-gate.mdc). Agents must satisfy **both** layers in § *Ship git consent (workflow + Sedea gate)* below.

## Ship git consent (workflow + Sedea gate)

Two **independent** layers apply on **implementation** lanes (`coding-session` and ship children). Satisfy **both**; neither substitutes for the other.

| Layer | Source | Controls | User grants via |
|-------|--------|----------|-----------------|
| **1 — Workflow** | § *Review before commit* (above) | Pause before advancing ship stage (summary, next skill, cut point) | **AskQuestion** — workflow-only options (*more changes*, *defer*, …) at cut-point; **auto-advance** after cut-point for pre-PR spawn, clean-go create-PR, and post-merge cleanup |
| **2 — Git history** | [`.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/6_git-commit-push-gate.mdc`](.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/6_git-commit-push-gate.mdc) | `git commit`, `git push`, PR steps that imply push | **Same user message** includes *commit* / *push*, **or** an **AskQuestion** pick on **that turn** whose `id` is `commit-only`, `executive-override-push`, or `commit-push-pr` (rule 6 § *After the user is satisfied*) — on **`coding-session`**, **`git push`** before **`pre-pr-review`** **`go`** requires **`executive-override-push`** or explicit same-message *push* per [`coding-session/SKILL.md`](../missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/coding-session/SKILL.md) § *Pre-PR ship gate (push/PR)* |

**Cross-turn rule:** A workflow **AskQuestion** pick in a **prior** turn does **not** authorize commit or push. Ship cut-point approval authorizes commit + Before deploy + **auto** pre-PR spawn on the **next** turn — it does **not** require a separate *run pre-pr-review* pick.

**When both layers apply in one turn**, use **one AskQuestion** with separate workflow options and git options (brief `label` text per [`.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/2_ask-question-instructions.mdc`](.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/2_ask-question-instructions.mdc)), **or** split turns: workflow **AskQuestion** first, then a **new** user message with *commit* / *push*.

| Developer need | Example workflow `options` | Example git `options` (layer 2 — same AskQuestion when committing this turn) |
|----------------|----------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Review only, no git yet | *More changes* · *Defer ship* · More details for option _ | Omit git options |
| Commit at cut-point (no push yet) | *More changes* · *Defer ship* · More details for option _ | *Commit only* · *No git actions* · More details for option _ |
| Push before pre-PR **`go`** | — | **Forbidden** in modals unless developer named **executive override** → **`executive-override-push`** on cut-point only |

Planning-tree picks use [`.sedea/centers/research-and-development/rules/30_planning-target-resolution.mdc`](30_planning-target-resolution.mdc) § *Sedea input channel* — not this table.

### AskQuestion vs git commit/push (same message)

| Developer signal (this turn or **AskQuestion** pick) | May continue workflow / spawn next skill? | May run **`git commit`**? | May run **`git push`**? |
|------------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------|---------------------------|-------------------------|
| *Proceed*, *next stage*, *looks good*, *approved cut point* (workflow only) | **Yes** — advance to commit + Before deploy on pick turn | **No** — unless the **same user message** also says *commit* (or equivalent) | **No** — unless the **same message** says *push* or *commit and push* |
| *Committed* / *ready for pre-PR review* (after implementation approval + commit + Before deploy when applicable) | **Yes** — **auto-spawn **`pre-pr-review`** per **`coding-session`** (no spawn modal) | **No** — unless the **same message** authorizes a **new** *commit* | **No** — until the **same message** says *push* |
| *commit*, *land the worktree*, *create a commit* in **same user message** | **Yes** | **Yes** (if there are changes to commit; skip if tree clean per cadence) | **No** — unless the message also says *push* |
| *push*, *commit and push*, *publish the worktree* in **same user message** | **Yes** | **Yes** when commit is included or already done | **Yes** |

If **AskQuestion** approved a workflow step in a **prior** turn, wait for a **new** user message containing *commit* / *push* before running git write commands. Clean **`pre-pr-review`** **`go`** authorizes inline **`create-pr`** on the **next** turn without a Create-PR modal — **not** commit or push consent.

### Mission-owned git when `plan and deliver` is active

When Mission Control dispatches **`plan and deliver`** on **research-and-development**, commit/push cut points in **this rule** and in **`coding-session`**, **`pre-pr-review`**, and **`create-pr`** count as **mission-owned git** per [`.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/6_git-commit-push-gate.mdc`](.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/6_git-commit-push-gate.mdc) § *Mission-owned git*.

| Situation | [`.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/6_git-commit-push-gate.mdc`](.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/6_git-commit-push-gate.mdc) § *Hosting-repo file edits* |
|-----------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| **`coding-session`** / ship child on hosting repo worktree | **Do not** duplicate rule-6 pre-edit or post-satisfaction AskQuestion for the same commit/push — follow **this rule** § *Review before commit* and the skill cadence |
| **`plan and deliver`** Squad Leader (planning only) | Usually no hosting-repo writes — rule 6 often N/A on that lane |
| Edits under **`.sedea/centers/`** on a **center-maintenance** or hosting dispatch | Rule 6 **applies** (not mission-owned) unless another mission owns git for that lane |

**Both layers still apply** on implementation lanes — see § *Ship git consent (workflow + Sedea gate)*. Ship cut-point approval is **not** commit or push consent by itself on the modal turn — **Act** runs on the response turn. Approving cut-point **does** authorize **auto** pre-PR spawn after commit + Before deploy complete.

## deploy-walk vs plan-reconcile (not chained)

Finishing **`deploy-walk`** (checklist complete, capstone todo **`deploy-test-plan-verified`** → `done`) does **not** start **`plan-reconcile`**.

| Skill | Ends when | Does **not** auto-start |
|-------|-----------|-------------------------|
| **`deploy-walk`** | Deploy §7 walked; Status `done` | **`plan-reconcile`** |
| **`plan-reconcile`** | Archive / follow-ups triage per **`plan-state.mjs`** | (nothing upstream) |

Start **`plan-reconcile`** separately: developer phrase on active **`coding-session`**, or **`coding-session`** [Plan-reconcile handoff (inline)](../missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/coding-session/SKILL.md#plan-reconcile-handoff-inline) after deploy when the developer **explicitly** chooses reconcile — see **`plan-reconcile/SKILL.md`** § *When this skill runs* and **development-process.md** § *Ship chain*.

## PR creation — inline **`create-pr`** on **`coding-session`**

**Rule (read first).** The **only** path that may call `gh pr create` (or any equivalent GitHub API/MCP call that creates, drafts, or reopens a PR) is the active **`coding-session`** agent **executing [`create-pr/SKILL.md`](../missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/create-pr/SKILL.md) inline** after **`pre-pr-review`** returns `go` and that skill's gates pass. Clean **`go`** runs inline **`create-pr`** **automatically** on the next turn ([Inline create-pr (auto on clean go)](../missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/coding-session/SKILL.md#inline-create-pr-auto-on-clean-go)); exceptional follow-up append uses [Create-PR handoff after go](../missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/coding-session/SKILL.md#create-pr-handoff-after-go).

| Lane | May call `gh pr create`? | Handoff |
|------|--------------------------|---------|
| **`coding-session`** running **`create-pr` inline** | **Yes** — sole supported opener | Load **`create-pr/SKILL.md`** on this lane after clean **`go`** auto path or exceptional Create-PR gate |
| **`coding-session`** (other steps) | **No** | Complete ship order through cut-point → Before deploy → **`pre-pr-review`** → inline **`create-pr`** |
| **Other lanes** (Squad Leader, planning, `pre-pr-review`, `pr-review`, `planner`, …) | **No** | Prepare worktree/context; direct developer to **`coding-session`** ship chain or emit copy-paste prompt — never open from the current lane |

**Developer accountability:** the developer decides **when** to open a PR and approves creation in the ship chain; **`coding-session`** runs inline **`create-pr`** (including `gh pr create` when authorized). Other lanes prepare context and hand off — they do not open GitHub themselves.

**All other lanes:** do **not** call `gh pr create` except **`coding-session`** while executing inline **`create-pr`** per the table above.

When the user or task says "open a PR", "push and open a PR", or "create a pull request" on a **non–`coding-session`** lane, interpret it as **hand off to the `coding-session` ship chain** — not as permission to run `gh pr create` on this lane.

### User phrases → required handoff (not `gh pr create`)

| User says (paraphrase OK) | Current lane | Required action |
|---------------------------|--------------|-----------------|
| *Open a PR* / *create the pull request* | **`coding-session`** before **`pre-pr-review`** **go** | **Do not** call `gh pr create`. Explain ship order: implementation review → cut-point (approve, commit, Before deploy **`deploy-walk`**) → auto **`pre-pr-review`** → inline **`create-pr`** on clean **go**. |
| *Open a PR* / *create the pull request* | **`coding-session`** after **`pre-pr-review`** clean **`go`** | Run inline **`create-pr`** automatically per § *Inline create-pr (auto on clean go)* in [`coding-session/SKILL.md`](../missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/coding-session/SKILL.md) — `gh pr create` only inside that procedure when gates pass. |
| *Open a PR* | Planning, Squad Leader, **`pre-pr-review`**, **`pr-review`**, **`planner`**, … | Prepare context; direct developer to **`coding-session`** ship chain — **never** `gh pr create` here. |
| *Push and open a PR* | **`coding-session`** | Run § *Commit and push cadence* (same-message *commit* / *push*) **first** when changes exist; then pre-PR / inline **`create-pr`** handoff — not one combined `gh pr create` step outside the inline procedure. |

This rule covers **chat output**, not just tool calls. After `git push`, do **not** surface or paraphrase GitHub's remote hint (the `Create a pull request for '<branch>' on GitHub by visiting: https://github.com/<org>/<repo>/pull/new/<branch>` line). That URL is the GitHub UI form and bypasses the protocol. The only PR-creation artifacts you present from other lanes are direction to **`coding-session`** or a copy-paste prompt for a future ship pass.

## Worktree setup in plans

Every multi-PR plan must end with a **Worktree setup** section containing copy-pasteable commands. Use the repo's directory name as a prefix for sibling worktree directories.

**Normative path (Mission Control and `coding-session`):** center **`worktree-setup.sh`** from **`HOSTING_ROOT`**, then MCP attach when the setup JSON hint reports **`nextAction: attach-required`**. **Forbidden on the default path:** inline **`git worktree add`**, **`sedea_add_worktree_folder`** before setup exits **0**, and default-path inline **`worktree-bootstrap`**. See [`coding-session/SKILL.md`](../missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/coding-session/SKILL.md) § *Generic flow (single repo)* and § *Center worktree scripts (binding)*.

Canonical form for creating a worktree with a new worktree name:

```bash
HOSTING_ROOT="<absolute-hosting-root>"
WORKTREE_ROOT="<absolute-sibling-path>"   # repo basename prefix per rule 7
WORKTREE_NAME="<worktree-name>"           # rule 7 / this rule § *Worktree naming*
BASE_REF="origin/main"

"$HOSTING_ROOT/.sedea/centers/sedea/scripts/worktree-setup.sh" \
  --hosting-root "$HOSTING_ROOT" \
  --worktree-path "$WORKTREE_ROOT" \
  --worktree-name "$WORKTREE_NAME" \
  --base-ref "$BASE_REF"
# Parse stdout JSON — bootstrapStatus success-class before implementation
# Mission Control: sedea_add_worktree_folder — absolute path to WORKTREE_ROOT when nextAction: attach-required
```

**Attach the worktree in Sedea.** In Mission Control chat, invoke MCP **`sedea_add_worktree_folder` only** with JSON `{ "path": "<absolute-worktree-root>" }` (optional `"name"` for the explorer label). Use an **absolute** `path`. **Forbidden:** editor **Add Folder to Workspace**, hand-edited **`.code-workspace`** attach, or calling **`sedea_add_worktree_folder`** **before** **`worktree-setup.sh`** exits **0**.

**Lane ownership:** On a spawned **`coding-session`** implementation lane, [Generic flow](../missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/coding-session/SKILL.md) steps 1–3 are normative. Map **`outputs.bootstrapStatus`** from setup JSON hints — **do not** run inline **`worktree-bootstrap`** after successful setup. Retry only per **`coding-session/SKILL.md`** § *Worktree bootstrap (inline mandatory)* when setup failed.

**Bootstrap inside setup (default).** Center **`worktree-setup.sh`** runs fast bootstrap per **`.cursor/rules/dot-sedea.mdc`** § *Worktree bootstrap mode* (`extensions-only-link`, `none`, or hosting overlay). **`coding-session`** sets **`outputs.bootstrapStatus: success`** from setup hints before implementation. On setup failure, ship phase stays at `worktree` until retry succeeds.

| Profile | When | Action |
|---------|------|--------|
| **Center setup (default)** | **`.sedea/centers/sedea/scripts/worktree-setup.sh`** on **`HOSTING_ROOT`** | Setup creates worktree + fast bootstrap; parse JSON hints |
| **Inline retry (exception)** | Setup failed or documented break-glass | **`worktree-bootstrap`** inline only — see deprecated skill + **`coding-session`** retry section |

**Push order (all profiles):** [`.cursor/rules/dot-sedea.mdc`](.cursor/rules/dot-sedea.mdc) § *Push before worktrees (mandatory)* and § *Submodule pins* when present; after center **`defaultBranch`** merges, § *Center submodule pin promotion (hosting repo)* below. Submodule init in a worktree uses the **committed** gitlink on that worktree's base ref — not an uncommitted pointer on the primary clone.

#### Hosting overlay reference (retry / legacy — not default path)

When center setup is unavailable or a documented retry invokes **`worktree-bootstrap`**, read [`.cursor/rules/dot-sedea.mdc`](.cursor/rules/dot-sedea.mdc) § *Worktree bootstrap mode* and **`./scripts/bootstrap-worktree-dev.sh --help`** on **`HOSTING_ROOT`**. **`full`** bootstrap escalation on the center setup path is **forbidden** (exit **11** warm-primary, exit **12** overlay missing).

**Detach merged worktrees from the workbench.** After a PR merges, on the **`coding-session`** lane run [Post-merge workspace cleanup](../missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/coding-session/SKILL.md#post-merge-workspace-cleanup) **before** After deploy `deploy-walk` — **only** for **this pass’s** **`WORKTREE_ROOT`** when § *Worktree removal ownership (binding)* preconditions all pass. Invoke **`sedea_remove_worktree_folder`** first, then center **`worktree-cleanup.sh`** with ownership attestation — **forbidden:** inline **`git worktree remove`** + **`git pull origin main`** on the default path when the center script applies.

Use **`origin/main`** as **`--base-ref`**, **not** local **`main`** — local **`main`** checked out elsewhere breaks naive worktree creation.

- For each **independent** PR, emit the **`worktree-setup.sh`** block above (or one command per worktree). These can be created and worked on immediately.
- For each **dependent** PR, emit the command but comment that it should be created only after the predecessor merges.
- Include cleanup for after PRs merge: for **this session’s** retired **`WORKTREE_ROOT` only** (§ *Worktree removal ownership (binding)*), **`sedea_remove_worktree_folder`** with that worktree's **absolute** path (Mission Control first), then **`worktree-cleanup.sh`** for **that path only** — **never** repo-wide **`git worktree prune`** or removal of other agents’ worktrees.
- In the **Worktree setup** narrative, after setup succeeds, tell the agent to invoke **`sedea_add_worktree_folder`** with that worktree's **absolute** path when **`nextAction: attach-required`**.

### Dirty hosting repo before center setup

[`coding-session/SKILL.md`](../missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/coding-session/SKILL.md) § *Generic flow* runs a **dirty-tree gate** inside center **`worktree-setup.sh`** (exit **10**). On hosting repos that pin `.sedea/` via git submodules (**.cursor/rules/dot-sedea.mdc** § *Submodule pins* on the active hosting repo), **submodule gitlink-only** porcelain under `.sedea/centers/` and `.sedea/operations/` does **not** block worktrees when `git diff --stat -- <submodule-path>` shows pointer-only drift (2 +/- per submodule). All other non-empty porcelain still blocks.

